task.summary: Added more gui functionality and added model classes and finished some methods in the Api class. Also added a method in MainPane to fade in and out the screens

Repush - all files werent added
Added more gui functionality and added model classes and finished some methods in the Api class. Also added a method in MainPane to fade in and out the screens
Minor changes: Changed login method in LogInController and added an animation to the text fields if they are empty when trying to log in. Also added PlayMenuPane

Worked on joinGame, startGame and deleteGame in ServerConnection.
Also added getCurrentUsersGames functionality in ServerConnection and connected it with the PlayMenuController and PlayMenuPane. The client now properly shows the games stored in the Session class in the TableView.
Session class now contains user specific ArrayLists of games and CachedData contain only data that is not user specific.
Played with css for the GUI

Login method in LogInController now spawns a new Thread when a user log in. The Thread repeatedly checks if the currentUser is still authenticated.
Get, Post, Put and Delete methods in ServerConnection now call the Logout method if a status code 401 Unauthorized is received in the response.
The Logout method sets all values of the Session to null and the Thread that was spawned when the user logged in will redirect the user back to the LogInPane.
Also made a little progress on the getOpenGames method

Added functionality for showOpenGames() in PlayMenuController. The user can now see all open joinable games, meaning the user isn't the host of these.
Also added functionality for playBtn and joinBtn in PlayMenuController - they now call ServerConnection's methods joinGame(). playBtn now sets a the selected game as a static variable and redirects the user to the PlayGamePane where the user can enter his/hers controls, press playBtn and get the result on a dialog box. When the user close the dialog box it is then redirected back to the PlayMenuPane where it can proceed with joining, playing or creating games.
Also made minor fixes such as renaming.

Added screen for creating games and functionality for it in the CreateGameController class. It is now possible to create games as either open game or invite another player from the table.
Also added delete button in PlayMenuPane and functionality in PlayMenuController. The user can now delete games that are not flagged "finished" if the user is a player in the game. Right now the user can delete games in which it is the opponent, however this might not be desirable as a user can exploit this to join and delete other players' open games. The reason a user is able to delete games as an opponent is that the player might have been invited to the game and doesn't want to play it.
Suggestion: Make it possible for players to leave games instead of deleting them.
